3. (1) Variables :

      --> It is used to store a value

      --> syntax:

             variable = value 

             eg: name = "Vikashini"  (here name is the variable and vikashini is the value.)


    --> Note: Python is a type-inferred language, so you don't have to explicitly define the variable type.


(2)  Variables Can Change:

age = 18
print(age)

age = 19
print(age)

Output:
18
19

--> Because variables are changeable.



(3) Rules for Naming Python Variables:
             
          -->   Cannot start with number
          -->   No spaces
          -->   Use _ instead of spaces
          -->   Cannot use keywords like if, for, while


(4)  CONSTANTS 

         --> Constants are values that should NOT change.

         --> Python doesn’t have real constants, but programmers write them in CAPITAL letters.

         -->  Example:

               PI = 3.14

        --> We treat it like fixed data.

